-- Undergraduate Applications to Penn Flat From Year Ago
-- B y   J a n e t   L o r i n
-- 2013-01-18T22:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-18/undergraduate-applications-to-penn-flat-from-year-ago.html
Undergraduate applications to the
 University of Pennsylvania  for the 2013-2014 academic year
increased by a single submission compared with a year ago.  The Ivy League school in Philadelphia received 31,219
applications, according to preliminary numbers, Eric Furda, dean
of undergraduate admissions, said in an e-mail. Last year, the
school got 31,218 applications.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Janet Lorin in New York 
 jlorin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lisa Wolfson at 
 lwolfson@bloomberg.net  